The paper proposes a novel reinforcement learning method that combines model-based and model-free approaches, with a focus on modeling uncertainty. This makes it likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Additionally, the paper deals with robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY), which are also likely categories. Finally, the paper uses ensemble methods and probabilistic models, which are common in the Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) category.
